of the impact of medicaid those who do not have health insurance tend to be different in many ways from people who have it says alan garber md head of stanford health policy new york times first study of its kind shows benefit of providing medical insurance to poor search chp search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest alan garber named provost of harvard april 15 2011 fsi stanford chp pcor news in new england journal commentary shp director alan garber explores the role of fda in regulating devices march 24 2010 announcement director alan garber discusses comparative effectiveness research at brookings event december 2 2009 announcement alan garber receives career achievement award from society for medical decision making november 11 2009 news director alan garber discusses patient care in nyt magazine article making health care better in the news new york times on november 8 2009 alan garber assesses what to expect from health reform october 14 2009 fsi stanford chp pcor news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 736 0815 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
